Summary of Material Information:

  • Sofdra™ Launch Performance:
  • Gross Sales: ~AUD $25 million cumulative (Jan-Jun 2025), with monthly growth.
  • Prescriptions: Over 16,000 TRx filled since launch (Feb 2025).
  • Prescriber Base: 2,300+ unique prescribers in June 2025 (up from 540 in Feb 2025).

  • Refill Rates: Exceeding industry average (3.4 fills per patient vs. 2 fills benchmark).

  • Gross-to-Net (GTN) Dynamics:

  • GTN yield improved to 23% (June 2025), target 30–40%.

  • Fully reimbursed claims grew 50% since launch; high-deductible claims declined 75%.

  • Commercial Strategy:

  • Sales Force Expansion: From 27 reps (Q3 2025) to 50 reps (Q2 2026).

  • Demand Drivers: HCP engagement, digital/media campaigns, peer-reviewed data (JAAD publication).

  • Benchmark Comparison:

  • Rep productivity (~AUD $81k net revenue/rep) exceeds early-stage peers (e.g., ZORYVE at ~USD $30k/rep).

No material capital raising, financial results, or trading halt details identified.

Key Material Information Summary

Performance & Positioning:

  • June 2025 Return: +5.8% (vs. ASX200AI +1.4%).
  • 5-Year Annualized Return: +21.0% p.a. (vs. ASX200AI +11.8% p.a.).
  • Portfolio Positioning: Strong value skew (median long P/E: 11x, ~8% FCF yield, double-digit EPS growth). Favors infrastructure, gold, copper, travel, and "quality value" stocks.

Key Contributors (Long Positions):

  • Santos (+16%): Non-binding takeover offer at A$8.89/sh (28% premium); Barossa/Pikka projects nearing completion.
  • Viva Energy (+16%): Recovery in retail fuel margins and volatile refining margins; OTR/Coles Express synergies expected.
  • James Hardie (+18%): Rebound post-Azek acquisition close; U.S. investor interest renewed.

Key Detractor:

  • Gold Investments: Pullback after strong 2025 performance; physical gold price consolidation.

Market Outlook:

  • ASX deemed "fully valued"; global equities (non-Australian) preferred for growth and valuation upside.

Exposure & Liquidity (30 June 2025):

  • NTA (after tax): $3.12/share.
  • Market Cap: $1.82bn.
  • Net Exposure: 77% (32% North America, 31% Europe).

No capital raising or material corporate action identified.

• Potential Equity Investment: German Raw Materials Fund (GRMF) appraisal phase initiated for €50m–€150m (target: €100m / ~A$175m) in Arafura’s Nolans Project, tied to NdPr supply.

  • Strategic Context: Complements existing A$200m commitment from Australia’s National Reconstruction Fund and US$115m Euler Hermes loan guarantee.

• Drilling Results: High-grade copper intercepts at Jericho Deposit, including:
  • Jolly Shoot (J1 Lens):
    • 7.0m @ 2.4% Cu & 0.4g/t Au
    • 6.0m @ 2.4% Cu & 1.8g/t Au
    • 7.2m @ 2.8% Cu & 0.5g/t Au (incl. 2.2m @ 7.6% Cu & 1.2g/t Au)
  • Tucker Shoot (J2 Lens):
    • 3.1m @ 3.0% Cu & 0.4g/t Au
    • 6.0m @ 1.8% Cu & 0.6g/t Au
  • Implications: Confirms high-grade mineralization near planned Jericho Link Drive, enhancing potential for early ore development. Mineralization remains open down-plunge.
  • Upcoming: Additional drilling results expected in coming months.
